object.script:
function onTick()
WP1X = input.getNumber(1) WP1Y = input.getNumber(2) WP2X = input.getNumber(3) WP2Y = input.getNumber(4) WP3X = input.getNumber(5) WP3Y = input.getNumber(6) WP4X = input.getNumber(7) WP4Y = input.getNumber(8) WP5X = input.getNumber(9) WP5Y = input.getNumber(10) WP6X = input.getNumber(11) WP6Y = input.getNumber(12) WP7X = input.getNumber(13) WP7Y = input.getNumber(14) WP8X = input.getNumber(15) WP8Y = input.getNumber(16) WP9X = input.getNumber(17) WP9Y = input.getNumber(18)
inputX = input.getNumber(23) inputY = input.getNumber(24) isPressed = input.getBool(30)
GPSX = input.getNumber(20) GPSY = input.getNumber(21) Zoom = input.getNumber(22)
isPressingRectangle1 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, w-18, 3, 15, 15) isPressingRectangle2 = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, w-18, 21, 15, 15)
output.setBool(1, isPressingRectangle1) output.setBool(2, isPressingRectangle2)
end
function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw()
w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
screen.drawMap(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom)
screen.setColor(0, 0, 0)
screen.drawTextBox(w-17, 4, 14, 14, "+", 0, 0) if isPressingRectangle1 then screen.drawRectF(w-18, 3, 15, 15) else screen.drawRect(w-18, 3, 15, 15) end
screen.drawTextBox(w-17, 22, 14, 14, "-", 0, 0) if isPressingRectangle2 then screen.drawRectF(w-18, 21, 15, 15) else screen.drawRect(w-18, 21, 15, 15) end
screen.setColor(255, 0, 0, 75)
pixelX, pixelY = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, GPSX, GPSY) screen.drawCircleF(pixelX, pixelY, 2)
if WP1X ~= 0 and WP1Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 0) end
WP1XP, WP1YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP1X, WP1Y)
screen.drawLine(pixelX, pixelY, WP1XP, WP1YP)
if WP2X ~= 0 and WP2Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 0) end
WP2XP, WP2YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP2X, WP2Y)
screen.drawLine(WP1XP, WP1YP, WP2XP, WP2YP)
if WP3X ~= 0 and WP3Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 0) end
WP3XP, WP3YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP3X, WP3Y)
screen.drawLine(WP2XP, WP2YP, WP3XP, WP3YP)
if WP4X ~= 0 and WP4Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 0) end
WP4XP, WP4YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP4X, WP4Y)
screen.drawLine(WP3XP, WP3YP, WP4XP, WP4YP)
if WP5X ~= 0 and WP5Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 0) end
WP5XP, WP5YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP5X, WP5Y)
screen.drawLine(WP4XP, WP4YP, WP5XP, WP5YP)
if WP6X ~= 0 and WP6Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 0) end
WP6XP, WP6YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP6X, WP6Y)
screen.drawLine(WP5XP, WP5YP, WP6XP, WP6YP)
if WP7X ~= 0 and WP7Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 0) end
WP7XP, WP7YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP7X, WP7Y)
screen.drawLine(WP6XP, WP6YP, WP7XP, WP7YP)
if WP8X ~= 0 and WP8Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(0, 255, 255, 0) end
WP8XP, WP8YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP8X, WP8Y)
screen.drawLine(WP7XP, WP7YP, WP8XP, WP8YP)
if WP9X ~= 0 and WP9Y ~= 0 then screen.setColor(255, 0, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(255, 0, 255, 0) end
WP9XP, WP9YP = map.mapToScreen(GPSX, GPSY, Zoom, w, h, WP9X, WP9Y)
screen.drawLine(WP8XP, WP8YP, WP9XP, WP9YP)
end

object.script:
-- -> 0deg V90deg <180deg ^270deg tyaw = 0 yawup = 1 targets = {} srans = {45,60,90,180} mode = 1 sran = srans[mode] touched = false
zoom = {5000,2500,1000,500,50} zoomMode = 1 clicked = false
found = {}
function onTick() inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) isPressed = input.getBool(1) tdis = input.getNumber(7) --sran = input.getNumber(8) --45d, 90d, 180d sspd = input.getNumber(8) --scanspeed tdet = input.getBool(3) --target detected revs = input.getBool(4) --downward?
if (math.abs(tyaw)>sran) and (sran~=180) then yawup = yawup*-1 end tyaw = tyaw + yawup*sspd/5 if tyaw>=180 then tyaw = -180 end
for i,v in ipairs(found) do v[3] = v[3]-1 if v[3]<0 then table.remove(found,i) end end
if tdet then table.insert(found, {tyaw, tdis, 255}) end
isPressingRectangle = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 2,2,8,8)
if isPressingRectangle then clicked = true end
if not isPressed then if clicked then zoomMode = (zoomMode+1)%#zoom clicked = false elseif touched then mode = (mode+1)%#srans yawup = 1 tyaw = 0 found = nil found = {} end end touched = isPressed sran = srans[mode+1]
if revs then output.setNumber(1, -tyaw/360) else output.setNumber(1, tyaw/360) end output.setNumber(2, radius) output.setNumber(3, centerH) end
function drawPixel(x, y) screen.drawText(x-1, y-4, ".") end
function drawArcDash(x, y, r, st, w) for i=st, (st+w)-1 do x1, y1 = x + r*math.cos(math.rad(i)), y + r*math.sin(math.rad(i)) drawPixel(x1,y1) end end
function drawBackground(x, y, r, st, w) local k = math.floor(math.log(r)) for i=1, k do drawArcDash(x, y, r*i/k, st, w) end if sran ~= 180 then x1, y1 = x + r*math.cos(math.rad(st)), y + r*math.sin(math.rad(st)) screen.drawLine(x, y, x1, y1) x1, y1 = x + r*math.cos(math.rad(st+w)), y + r*math.sin(math.rad(st+w)) screen.drawLine(x, y, x1, y1) end end
function drawButton(x,y,w,h) if clicked then screen.setColor(255,255,0) else screen.setColor(0,64,0) end screen.drawRect(x, y, w, h) screen.drawTextBox(x+1, y+1, w, h, "R", 0, 0) end
function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() screenH, screenW = screen.getHeight(), screen.getWidth() screen.setColor(0,32,0)
if sran ~= 180 then radius = screenW/(2*math.sin(math.rad(sran)))*0.9 else radius = screenH/2*0.9 end centerH = screenH/2 + screenH*(180-sran)/300
drawBackground(screenW/2, centerH, radius, 270-sran, 2*sran)
x3, y3 = screenW/2 + radius*math.cos(math.rad(tyaw-90)), centerH + radius*math.sin(math.rad(tyaw-90)) screen.drawLine(screenW/2, centerH, x3, y3)
--screen.drawText(0,0,screenW.."x"..screenH) --screen.drawText(0, 0, sran*2) screen.drawTextBox(0, 0, screenW, screenH, zoom[zoomMode+1].."m", 1, -1)
for i, v in ipairs(found) do screen.setColor(0, 255, 0, v[3]) xt, yt = screenW/2 + radius*v[2]/zoom[zoomMode+1]*math.cos(math.rad(v[1]-90)), centerH + radius*v[2]/zoom[zoomMode+1]*math.sin(math.rad(v[1]-90)) drawPixel(xt, yt) end
--screen.drawText(screenW/2, centerH, tyaw)
drawButton(2,2,8,8)
end
